dcterms:description: The Imagenet dataset is a large visual database designed for use in visual object recognition software research. It contains over 14 million images categorized into thousands of classes.
dcterms:title: Imagenet dataset

dcterms:description: The VIPriors Image Classification Challenge dataset is used for training models to achieve high accuracy in image classification tasks, specifically on the Imagenet dataset.
dcterms:title: VIPriors Image Classification Challenge

dcterms:creator: E. D. Cubuk
B. Zoph
D. Mane
dcterms:description: AutoAugment is a data augmentation strategy that learns augmentation policies from the data itself, enhancing the performance of image classification models.
dcterms:title: AutoAugment

dcterms:creator: E. D. Cubuk
B. Zoph
J. Shlens
dcterms:description: RandAugment is a practical automated data augmentation technique that simplifies the search space for augmentation policies, improving model performance.
dcterms:title: RandAugment

dcterms:creator: S. Yun
D. Han
S. J. Oh
dcterms:description: Cutmix is a data augmentation strategy that combines two images by cutting and pasting patches from one image to another, mixing their labels proportionally.
dcterms:title: Cutmix
